'''Elphinstone Research Centre''' is a medical research centre east of [[Edinburgh]], south of [[Tranent]], in [[East Lothian]].
==History== In the 1970s it was the site of Inveresk Research International.<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=New Scientist|publisher=Reed Business Information|issn=0262-4079|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=LVNxl7T-id4C&pg=PA1053|page=1053|accessdate=2016-01-07}}</ref> Inveresk had been founded in 1957 and was situated in the former offices of the [[Institute of Seaweed Research]].
==Structure== It is situated to the south of Tranent, between the B6414 and B6371, north-east of [[Elphinstone, East Lothian|Elphinstone]]. The site employs around 750 people.
==Function== It conducts medical research.
